According to the Risk Analysis Division of the Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, constituted in August of this year with the support of the Movement for a Better Hungary, has increased political risk in Hungary and the region from several points of view.
The company’s “Risk Warning” states: “With the exacerbation of ethnic tensions between the Gita and non-Gita population of Hungary, even violent ethnic confrontations can occur in the short term.”
The main reason for this is that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard is likely to be the provocation of an event of this nature – added the representative of the research institute.
They stated that this was due to one of the main shortcomings of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life gave the public debate of the gypsy problem to representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who could base their political strategy on the existing Huns and gypsy discrepancies".
This aggravates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of violent conflicts.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international average, “has significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, especially with regard to the stability and democratic development of the country.”
We are reminded that: since the fall of 2006, the reorganization of the radical and far-right groups of Hungary has received increasing publicity and impulse, and that since the summer of 2007 numerous organizations have been set up in the country that define themselves as "national self-defense associations".
"The common feature of these groups is that they define themselves as civil organizations, while openly proclaiming the training of their members for defense - even armed - (civil defense, national defense, public order), referring to the ineptitudes of the police, the army, i.e. the state."
They claimed that all this was done in accordance with the method that attempts to give a civil presentation to different political aspirations, based on the dissatisfaction of society with politics and with political parties.
