The Act also requires investment service companies to disclose information on key aspects of their business profile, exposure to risk and forms of risk management in the market and requires them to keep a record of all transactions they perform, in order to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
In its passage by the Congressional Economic Commission, several amendments were incorporated, including highlighting that securitized debts are considered as a "complex" financial instrument given its high risk to the investor, which has been demonstrated by what happened with the U.S. high-risk mortgage debt.
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally delimit the functions that graduates in Economics and Business can develop 30 years after the actual decree delimiting the professional functions reserved for economists was passed in 1977.
