Car insurance, which covers the driver in case of possible accidents, is an important expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, age of the passport, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of it, among others.
Having a car is just the beginning.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is realized in an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the amount of the agreed premium in exchange for being responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in case of accident.
The premium is the insurance price, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, age of the card, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or its use, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the more likely they are to suffer an accident, the higher the fee to be paid.
That’s why both older than 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics reflect that they have a lower rate of accidentality due to their prudence.
Also, by taking the counts, companies have come to the conclusion that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use that is given to the vehicle will influence the frequency, and thereby the likelihood of having some kind of percance.
As the frequency increases, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the price of the premium.
That is why the driver must carefully study the situation to choose the car insurance that best fits his profile.
Here we will expose the most significant variables when choosing one or another type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers you a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various drawbacks when contracting insurance at an affordable price, such as reduced driving experience and old age.
Although the ideal for being well-insured is all-risk insurance, there are other more economical options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for a whole-risk franchise, so they get insurance coverage at all-risk but at a more feasible price.
This type of agreement would require the customer to pay a part of the amount of the sin.
“The portion of the amount of the sin of the customer will be pre-established based on the value of the premium, which will be the higher the lower the amount,” says Luis Noguera, Spain’s top-ranked First Europe insurance broker.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer ensures protection against damage caused to third parties, although not against those caused in his own car.
In addition, it would be covered by theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A tip.
If you are under the age of 25 try to be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, which can reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate owned by the company.
On the contrary, a penalty is a surcharge on such a base rate.
“The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its benefit.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses,” explains Noguera.
After the 25-year-old streak, drivers make it easier to hire insurance, as the accident rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is most advisable to engage a whole risk with a franchise.
“Normally, young people can’t take advantage of the experience previously gained in an accident, and even in driving,” says the director in Spain of the European company, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, once the ‘fear of the novice’ has passed.
However, if the client is married but still has no children, it is preferable to negotiate insurance at all risk, as long as their economic situation allows it, of course it is.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be the public with the lowest sinisterity rate, so the charges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be one at all risk with a franchise (may be 300 euros), or, when a high level of bonus is available, one to third parties extended from the third year of the vehicle life.
“They carry out a more relaxed driving and have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchise,” said Luis Noguera.
For retirees it is advisable to have insurance at all risk with a franchise (being this one of 150 euros), or one to third parties expanded when you have a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is important, not only because it covers the driver in the event of possible accidents, but also because it represents an important expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that best suits us according to our personal situation.
